HEADWORD: Torchwort
<hw>Torch"wort`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>The common mullein, the stalks of which, dipped in suet, anciently
served for torches. Called also <altname>torch</altname>, and
<altname>hig-taper</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tore</ent>⟦br⟧
